-I don't know what he said.

26:19.529 --> 26:22.202
He said if the bottom falls out.

26:22.369 --> 26:27.443
This filthy, roach-ridden reality
is inspiring.

26:29.649 --> 26:32.880
What did that cop say
when he grabbed your throat?

26:33.049 --> 26:37.042
-I don't fucking believe you!
-" I don't fucking believe you."

26:37.209 --> 26:39.359
-Fabulous!
-You don't get it.

26:39.529 --> 26:42.362
Think this is
The Count of Monte Cristo?

26:42.529 --> 26:45.646
This is the real deal.
We're in deep shit.

26:45.809 --> 26:49.358
You and I are innocent.
You know that. I know that.

26:49.529 --> 26:53.727
The two guys who really pulled
that bank job know it too.

26:53.889 --> 26:55.925
But the cops don't know it!

26:56.089 --> 26:58.125
Donahue. Monroe.

26:58.289 --> 27:02.601
-I am entitled to a private interview.
-Forget it.

27:07.209 --> 27:09.677
-Are you here for us?
-I believe so.

27:09.849 --> 27:13.080
I'm Skip Donahue.
This is my buddy, Harry Monroe.

27:13.249 --> 27:17.003
-I'm Len Garber, your lawyer.
-It's a pleasure to see you.

27:17.169 --> 27:21.242
Call my girlfriend, Cindy Laurence.
They won't let me.

27:21.409 --> 27:23.445
-It's important to him.
-I will.

27:23.609 --> 27:27.488
-Say we're at our cousins.
-There's been a misunderstanding.

27:27.649 --> 27:30.686
I am more or less familiar
with the case.

27:30.849 --> 27:32.646
You know we're innocent?

27:32.809 --> 27:35.801
Can't you just cut through
all this garbage?

27:35.969 --> 27:39.200
This isn't funny.
Do they know I hate confinement?

27:39.369 --> 27:44.443
They don't care. I can only shower
them with motions. I've filed two.

27:44.609 --> 27:47.077
-Only two?
-How about a dozen on me?

27:47.249 --> 27:49.763
We're dealing with robbery
and assault.

27:49.929 --> 27:52.682
You might as well have
burned the Pentagon!

27:54.249 --> 27:56.558
Will the defendants rise?

27:58.089 --> 28:01.718
Considering the arguments
presented by both counsel...

28:02.009 --> 28:04.045
...and after deliberation...

28:04.209 --> 28:07.519
...l find the defendants
guilty as charged.

28:07.689 --> 28:11.364
Do you wish to waive the right
to a pre-sentence hearing?

28:11.529 --> 28:12.928
-No.
-Yes, Your Honour.

28:13.089 --> 28:16.365
Considering the ruthless nature
of this crime...

28:16.529 --> 28:19.601
...and the bleak prospects
for rehabilitation...

28:19.769 --> 28:23.205
...l hereby sentence you
to serve 1 25 years...

28:23.369 --> 28:28.284
...in the custody of the commissioner
of the Department of Corrections.

28:30.289 --> 28:32.405
Wait. No, no, no, wait.

28:32.569 --> 28:34.002
No, no, sit. Sit.

28:34.169 --> 28:37.002
We didn't do it.
There's a misunderstanding.

28:37.169 --> 28:39.000
-Right.
-We didn't do it.

28:39.169 --> 28:42.639
-Our lawyer told us to come up--
-I know I didn't.

28:42.809 --> 28:46.597
He's joking. He means we didn't do it.
We didn't do it.

28:46.769 --> 28:50.648
-Have you got the right case?
-This is Monroe and Donahue.

28:50.809 --> 28:55.405
-Harry Monroe. Look under there.
-Sir.

28:55.569 --> 28:58.129
-A tall, black man--
-Sir, we didn't--

28:58.289 --> 29:01.281
How much does that mean
in actual time?

29:01.449 --> 29:04.361
-Thirty years, tops.
-I'll be a dead old man.

29:04.529 --> 29:07.726
-Thirty years.
-I don't want to do one.

29:07.889 --> 29:11.199
I don't even want to do 100.
I can't....

29:11.369 --> 29:13.405
I'm gonna kill this mother.

29:15.529 --> 29:19.568
-I'm mad about what happened.
-It's not the end of the world.

29:19.729 --> 29:22.960
-What do we do?
-Start your sentence. I'll appeal.

29:23.129 --> 29:27.486
-A hundred and twenty-five years!
-Stop it! It's only 30 years.

29:27.689 --> 29:32.888
Can you get your staff to track down
those guys who really pulled it off?

29:33.049 --> 29:37.281
It's a one-man show. My cousin
is visiting from Massachusetts.

29:37.449 --> 29:39.963
She's a terrific social worker.
Bright.

29:40.129 --> 29:43.007
Oh, 1 25 years.
I won't have grandchildren!

30:12.649 --> 30:14.002
Thanks.

30:27.049 --> 30:31.201
It's chilling. It's frighteningly real.
It's almost surreal.

30:31.369 --> 30:35.487
Will you shut up until we get out
of this mess you got us into?

30:35.729 --> 30:38.562
Let's go. And no slow bucking.

30:38.729 --> 30:42.608
-Sir, how come--?
-Shut up, asshole, and move out!

30:48.769 --> 30:53.763
This is from the Middle Ages.
How do they expect you to move?

30:53.929 --> 30:56.568
I bet this whole thing is illegal.

30:56.729 --> 31:01.007
-Sir, wasn't this whole contraption--?
-Keep moving, turkey!

31:01.169 --> 31:02.887
Get up. Get up!

31:04.329 --> 31:07.639
You're gonna have to learn
the hard way, fella.

31:08.969 --> 31:11.847
I was right.
This is illegal and he knows it.

31:12.209 --> 31:15.007
Jesus! The man
ain't never gonna learn.

31:15.169 --> 31:17.842
Maybe after they hit him a few times.

31:18.009 --> 31:21.763
Just get into the flow of it.
Don't fight the metal.

31:21.929 --> 31:23.806
I'm not. It's fighting me.

31:23.969 --> 31:28.838
-What you up for, Sweetpants?
-We're innocent. I swear we are.

31:29.009 --> 31:31.887
My name ain't no goddamn "Sweetpants."

31:32.049 --> 31:33.801
Holy shit!

31:36.209 --> 31:39.758
-I have the swing of it now. Thanks.
-Sure.

31:39.929 --> 31:42.238
-I'm Skip Donahue.
-Jesus Ramirez.

31:42.409 --> 31:44.639
Nice to meet you.
Why are you here?

31:44.809 --> 31:48.597
I've been here seven years,
away from my beautiful Teresa.

31:48.769 --> 31:51.966
I was in court on an appeal hearing.
Lost again.

31:52.129 --> 31:54.768
They accused me
of robbing several banks.

31:54.929 --> 31:58.922
I was drunk, but I'm positive
I only robbed one bank. You?

31:59.089 --> 32:02.161
My friend and I were doing
a song and dance act.

32:02.329 --> 32:04.638
Must have been pretty bad.

32:12.009 --> 32:15.479
Excuse me. I'm not very good
at these written tests.

32:15.649 --> 32:20.404
I think you'll get much more of my
original flavour in an oral exam--

32:20.569 --> 32:24.721
You know, I'm just about to lose
my patience with you.

32:24.889 --> 32:28.677
-I was trying to explain--
-Keep writing, shitface!

32:33.249 --> 32:35.524
Two pears, three apples....

32:35.689 --> 32:40.399
Listen. A kid tried that on me once
at Camp Minikani in Vermont.

32:40.569 --> 32:44.608
I hit him so hard his braces
ripped his whole upper lip.

32:44.769 --> 32:48.603
His mother had to come get him
in the middle of the season.

33:06.129 --> 33:09.007
-What do they put in the dollhouses?
-Guess.

33:09.169 --> 33:12.400
-Us?
-Yes. You got it on the first try.

33:12.689 --> 33:14.168
-Harry.
-What?

33:15.289 --> 33:18.565
-We're in prison.
-Welcome to the real world!

33:18.729 --> 33:23.564
And not a minute too soon,
I might add. Now, brace up. Be strong.

33:44.169 --> 33:46.000
-Harry.
-What?

33:46.169 --> 33:48.808
I don't think I'm going to make it.

33:49.889 --> 33:53.677
Hang on, man. Don't mess up.
Just think about our appeal.

33:55.209 --> 33:57.404
Skip, please.

34:10.168 --> 34:12.125
Excuse me. Could I please--?

34:12.289 --> 34:15.326
Wait a minute,
I'm not a troublemaker.

34:17.529 --> 34:18.848
Skip.

34:24.289 --> 34:25.608
Skip!

34:26.849 --> 34:28.601
Okay, no more hitting.

34:28.768 --> 34:32.364
Did you hear what I said?
No more hitting. Turn around.

34:32.529 --> 34:34.963
Wanna stay late tonight?
Turn around.

34:35.129 --> 34:39.007
Let's get out of here!
Come on, Silver! Harry, I'm freaking.

34:39.168 --> 34:41.444
Giddyap! So long, suckers!

34:41.609 --> 34:44.521
Hey, Harry, he thinks he's a horse.

34:44.688 --> 34:46.088
Help me! Harry!

34:46.248 --> 34:48.399
Don't hit him! Please, he's sick.

34:48.569 --> 34:52.527
He's having a fit.
He don't have his fit pills.

34:52.688 --> 34:56.648
-He's got them, honest. Vietnam....
-Harry, help me, Harry!

34:56.809 --> 34:58.481
-Skip!
-Help!

35:00.289 --> 35:02.564
Oh, shit, Skip.

35:08.849 --> 35:13.240
It's okay. It's okay.
You did it. You did it.

35:13.409 --> 35:16.845
-He's okay now.
-I'm okay now. It's out of my system.

35:17.009 --> 35:18.203
-You okay?
-Yep.

35:18.369 --> 35:20.360
-He's okay.
-I'm 100 percent.

35:20.529 --> 35:22.121
Please, just this once.

35:22.289 --> 35:25.087
I mean, it's okay. Pretend it's okay.

35:25.249 --> 35:26.602
Okay.

35:26.769 --> 35:28.999
-He's okay, see?
-Yeah, we're okay.

35:29.169 --> 35:31.364
-Okay?
-Yeah.

35:35.569 --> 35:38.641
For God's sake!
You're gonna get us in trouble.

35:38.809 --> 35:42.518
-Harry, it's all right.
-I can't take it! Mama!

35:42.689 --> 35:44.168
-Come here.
-Mama!

35:44.329 --> 35:47.526
Take your pill.
Three seconds, it's over.

35:47.689 --> 35:52.126
One thousand one. One thousand two.
One thousand three. Finished!

35:52.289 --> 35:54.245
Finished!

35:54.409 --> 35:57.606
What did I tell you?
Okay, let's go.

35:57.769 --> 36:00.647
Back in line. Here we go.
Thanks very much.

36:00.849 --> 36:05.320
-Okay! Here we go. What's next?
-This way.

36:11.969 --> 36:14.403
I'd like spareribs, French fries...

36:14.649 --> 36:19.325
...and a big old juicy cheeseburger
on the side with a chocolate malt!

36:19.569 --> 36:20.684
Thanks.

36:21.169 --> 36:24.081
I can get you things,
like a cheeseburger.

36:24.289 --> 36:27.281
I don't want you
to get me no cheeseburger.

36:27.769 --> 36:30.761
-I'll wash your socks.
-Don't wash my socks.

36:30.969 --> 36:34.644
You leave my socks alone, man.
Stay out of my face.

36:41.009 --> 36:42.522
These are delicious.

36:42.729 --> 36:47.519
Aren't you amazed at the quality
of these vegetables? ln a prison?

36:47.729 --> 36:50.607
I'm amazed at what's
crawling in our soup.

36:50.809 --> 36:53.960
-What are you talking about?
-Little creatures.

36:54.169 --> 36:56.046
-Where?
-There.

37:27.169 --> 37:30.684
What's his story?
Why does he get a separate table?

37:30.889 --> 37:36.088
That's Grossberger. The biggest killer
in the history of the Southwest.

37:36.289 --> 37:40.567
He killed his whole family and all
his relatives in one weekend.

37:40.769 --> 37:44.364
Then he killed some people
who reminded him of them.

37:44.569 --> 37:49.085
-He here for rehabilitation?
-He threw the chaplain through a wall...

37:49.289 --> 37:53.168
...burned down the factory.
But he hasn't killed anyone here.

37:53.369 --> 37:57.726
I wouldn't sit with him,
and I killed my stepdaddy.

37:57.929 --> 38:03.720
I wonder what triggered all that
violence. He seems so gentle.

38:23.129 --> 38:24.767
I see what it is.

38:24.969 --> 38:30.965
Nobody has ever just sat down
and honestly talked with that man.

38:34.249 --> 38:39.767
-Poor kid.
-The man's not ready for an interview.

38:55.529 --> 38:56.848
Hello.

39:00.849 --> 39:05.286
I'll wait till after
he's had a little nap.

39:05.489 --> 39:09.368
Do you mind? Why did you
kill your stepfather anyway?

39:09.569 --> 39:14.962
Criticizing my new fur jacket.
And slapping my hand.

39:48.889 --> 39:52.325
-What should we do with him, Jack?
-How late was he?

39:52.529 --> 39:53.962
A week.

39:55.249 --> 40:00.004
You snort up all that nice blow
and then you forget about paying.

40:00.249 --> 40:03.161
Teach him to be punctual.

40:20.689 --> 40:23.681
-What was that all about?
-That's Jack Graham.

40:23.889 --> 40:25.845
You don't mess with him.

40:26.049 --> 40:30.600
-A guard can yank you out like that?
-He's an inmate like you and me.

40:30.809 --> 40:34.085
He runs the cellblock.
Dope, whiskey, a woman.

40:34.289 --> 40:38.680
He can get you anything you want.
And he can get you killed.

40:38.889 --> 40:42.802
Well, I don't want anything from him.

40:42.969 --> 40:48.487
That's Blade. He runs the Third World
side of cellblock two.

40:48.689 --> 40:53.683
Before Grossberger, he held the
axe-murder record in the Southwest.

40:53.889 --> 40:55.686
It's hard to be the best.

40:55.889 --> 40:59.882
He's gonna give me the cheeseburger.
How do you like it?

41:00.089 --> 41:03.684
I don't want a cheeseburger.
I'm watching my weight.

41:03.889 --> 41:05.800
-Don't worry.
-Getting fat.

41:06.009 --> 41:10.878
-I'll protect you. I make him uneasy.
-I wonder why.

41:12.049 --> 41:16.884
Hi. I'm going. Skip, my friend.
Excuse me, would you?

41:17.089 --> 41:19.364
-I'll come with you.
-Oh, shit.

41:22.009 --> 41:26.127
I'm a little nervous.
Did you sleep any better last night?

41:26.329 --> 41:30.038
A little between nightmares.
The walls close in on me.

41:30.249 --> 41:35.118
I know. I have it on the list. Roomier
cells, soap dish, toilet seats--

41:35.329 --> 41:37.479
What are you talking about?

41:41.089 --> 41:43.239
-That's ridiculous.
-Put that on your list.

41:43.449 --> 41:47.362
-I will. Unnecessary violence.
-See what they did to him?

41:47.569 --> 41:49.161
Okay, you two, inside.

41:57.329 --> 42:05.725
-Inmates 65984 and 65985.
-The New Yorkers.

42:05.929 --> 42:08.841
How do you do, sir?
Very nice to meet you.

42:09.049 --> 42:12.280
We'd like to touch--
I think I speak for Harry.

42:12.489 --> 42:14.047
-Would like to--
-No.

42:16.209 --> 42:20.088
Harry's a little nervous,
and I am a little bit too.

42:20.329 --> 42:23.127
This is a different
way of life for us.

42:23.369 --> 42:26.122
We'd like to discuss
with you some ideas...

42:26.369 --> 42:29.327
...we think would make
life easier for all.

42:29.569 --> 42:34.882
-Oh, do we have to listen to this?
-Were you in the middle of something?

42:35.089 --> 42:41.198
No. Mr. Wilson just doesn't feel the
same need to be hospitable as I do.

42:41.449 --> 42:43.326
Get on the bull!

42:43.569 --> 42:47.357
-Get on the ball?
-Get on the bull!

42:48.649 --> 42:54.440
Is that what that is? I didn't know.
Oh, is that a recreational activity?

42:54.649 --> 42:57.288
I was hoping for volleyball or tennis.

42:57.489 --> 43:01.528
We have an annual prison rodeo
we're awfully proud of.

43:01.729 --> 43:05.119
We like to run you new
fellas through a test...

43:05.369 --> 43:08.406
...to see if you have any
aptitude for it.

43:08.609 --> 43:10.247
Sure. Fine with me.

43:10.449 --> 43:14.840
-Be sure we don't miss some rodeo star.
-You don't need me, right?

43:15.049 --> 43:17.040
-You wanna shut up?
-Okay.

43:17.249 --> 43:21.288
-Okay, let her rip.
-You're on backwards.

43:24.249 --> 43:25.364
Okay.

43:28.689 --> 43:31.806
Over the rigging.

43:32.009 --> 43:34.443
I thought you meant the other way.

43:34.649 --> 43:38.358
I was looking for the
horns to come out. Okay.

43:38.569 --> 43:40.525
-You ready, Mr. Wilson?
-Ready.

43:40.769 --> 43:42.441
Proceed.

43:48.169 --> 43:52.208
Harry, you gotta try this.
It's fun.

43:52.409 --> 43:55.606
It's like the merry-go-round
at Coney lsland.

43:55.809 --> 43:57.686
Try two level.

44:05.249 --> 44:09.128
Where's the part where I go,
" Hee-ya"?

44:09.369 --> 44:11.246
Go to three.

44:17.049 --> 44:19.119
This is fun.

44:34.809 --> 44:36.765
Look, Ma. I'm dancing.

44:53.889 --> 44:55.880
Ride it, Skip!

45:07.369 --> 45:10.566
Ride that son of a bitch!

45:37.649 --> 45:38.968
All right.

45:46.649 --> 45:51.359
-Is it all right if I get off now?
-Yes. You can get off now.

45:54.049 --> 45:57.200
You two fellas can
go on back to your cells.

45:57.449 --> 45:58.723
Mr. Barstow!

45:58.929 --> 46:02.638
-We had a nice visit, didn't we?
-Yeah. Mr. Barstow!

46:02.849 --> 46:07.365
Here are the ideas I mentioned.
Why don't you chew on these?

46:07.569 --> 46:10.129
When you're ready, we'll go over them.

46:10.369 --> 46:13.884
-Get rid of them.
-Maybe we can meet for lunch.

46:15.089 --> 46:19.002
-I don't believe what I saw.
-The machine's malfunctioning!

46:19.209 --> 46:22.087
The machine's fine.
You want to try it?

46:22.289 --> 46:24.519
-It was luck.
-He's a born cowboy.

46:24.729 --> 46:27.880
-From New York?
-I don't care where he's from.

46:28.089 --> 46:30.887
No inmate ever took it to six level.

46:31.089 --> 46:36.800
Your big rodeo star, Graham,
never got it past a four.

46:37.049 --> 46:41.088
-Graham's had injuries.
-I've had 10 years of humiliation!

46:41.289 --> 46:44.087
I won't mention the money
trouble I'm in...

46:44.289 --> 46:48.601
...from losing to Warden Sampson
and his gorillas, because of him!

46:48.809 --> 46:53.360
If that kid's for real, he'll ride
for Glenboro in the next rodeo...

46:53.569 --> 46:57.926
...and we're gonna whip Sampson's boys
and win that goddamn prize!

46:58.169 --> 47:04.358
Get that kid back here in an hour.
I wanna test him on Double Aught again.

47:04.569 --> 47:08.244
-Check it out.
-You check it out.

47:13.969 --> 47:18.247
My back hurts, fellas,
I'm gonna have to drop out.

47:20.289 --> 47:22.086
Okay.

47:23.529 --> 47:28.045
My back still hurts from yesterday.
Hurt it again.

47:28.249 --> 47:32.481
Harry, rub me a little bit,
right here, would you? That's it.

47:35.169 --> 47:39.321
That's better. Did you try that
thing in the warden's office?

47:39.529 --> 47:40.723
-It's fun.
-It is.

47:40.969 --> 47:44.757
Jesus was the champion
bull rider from his province.

47:44.969 --> 47:49.679
You're kidding! That's wonderful.
Are you gonna ride in the rodeo?

47:49.889 --> 47:53.962
-Jesus says the rodeo is bullshit.
-Why? How come?

47:54.169 --> 47:58.685
Do you know how much money
they make on it? $85,000 to $100,000.

47:58.889 --> 48:00.925
Hundred thousand dollars.

48:01.129 --> 48:04.599
We're supposed to get the money.
We don't get shit.

48:04.809 --> 48:07.881
We get our ass kicked. They get rich.

48:08.089 --> 48:11.525
The prisoners don't get one
penny of that money?

48:11.729 --> 48:14.880
No, I'm exaggerating a little,
I guess.

48:15.089 --> 48:19.401
Two years ago we got new
Ping-Pong balls. Five boxes.

48:19.649 --> 48:24.086
I don't understand one thing.
Why do the guys go to the rodeo?

48:24.329 --> 48:28.527
They scare everybody by threatening
to deny their parole.

48:28.769 --> 48:32.205
-That's how they get the kiss-asses.
-Outrageous!

48:32.449 --> 48:38.684
In Texas, they run an honest rodeo.
The prisoners keep the prize money.

48:38.929 --> 48:43.684
Them wardens over there are pretty
decent. Not like these pricks.

48:43.889 --> 48:46.278
Isn't that fucking outrageous?

48:46.649 --> 48:50.927
Say, I hear you went to six
on Double Aught, hey?

48:51.169 --> 48:56.163
-He's my man.
-Did you tell him? It wasn't so tough.

48:56.369 --> 48:59.679
Well, if you really did a six...

48:59.929 --> 49:04.525
...they're gonna want you to ride
in that Top Hand competition.

49:04.769 --> 49:06.999
Don't worry. I'm no brown-noser.

49:07.209 --> 49:11.282
Everybody knows that.
Why don't you hear the man out?

49:11.529 --> 49:17.525
If you ride in the Top Hand event,
there's a good chance we can bust out.

49:17.769 --> 49:20.237
You know what I mean?

49:31.369 --> 49:36.124
-Is he talking about a jailbreak--?
-You bet your ass.

49:37.129 --> 49:42.522
-What about our appeal?
-Appeal? Rory, tell him about appeals.

49:42.769 --> 49:48.127
The day I met you and Sweetpants was
my fifth appeal hearing in six years.

49:48.369 --> 49:49.722
Turned me down.

49:49.969 --> 49:54.008
Do you want to spend 30 years in here?
I couldn't take it.

49:54.249 --> 49:57.878
And I know you can't.
We gotta get out of here.

50:01.529 --> 50:07.923
Hello, operator, get me Warden Sampson
at Doerin Prison, please. Thank you.

50:08.289 --> 50:12.328
Hello, Wally.
How's your team look this year?

50:12.569 --> 50:16.084
