01:20:31.249 --> 01:20:36.243
Operator? Please get me the sheriff's
office. This is an emergency.

01:20:47.209 --> 01:20:49.040
I've been looking for you.

01:20:49.289 --> 01:20:51.200
-Where've you been?
-Look at this.

01:20:51.369 --> 01:20:56.124
It's so simple it is absurd.
It should be laughed out of court.

01:20:56.289 --> 01:20:58.120
We'll talk about that later.

01:20:58.329 --> 01:21:01.287
-They're gonna kill your clients.
-They're innocent!

01:21:01.449 --> 01:21:04.361
That's not the point.
I'll explain it later.

01:21:04.569 --> 01:21:06.525
We have to get to the rodeo.

01:21:06.689 --> 01:21:08.839
It's across town.
We'll never make it.

01:21:09.009 --> 01:21:11.887
We have to try.
Will you shut up and hurry?

01:21:12.049 --> 01:21:15.485
I almost blew it.
How can I call myself a lawyer?

01:21:34.489 --> 01:21:36.366
That's it for the preliminaries.

01:21:36.609 --> 01:21:39.601
Get ready for the event
that you all came to see.

01:21:39.769 --> 01:21:44.365
It's our featured event,
the Top Hand competition.

01:21:47.729 --> 01:21:51.608
-How's your secret weapon, Wally?
-Fit as a fiddle, Henry.

01:21:51.849 --> 01:21:55.000
-It's a nice day for it, ain't it?
-Sure is.

01:21:55.649 --> 01:22:01.360
-Come on down, got your Coke here....
-Peanuts, popcorn....

01:23:25.289 --> 01:23:29.077
Now remember, spur him high
on the shoulders, okay?

01:23:29.249 --> 01:23:30.967
Try to keep a good rhythm.

01:23:31.129 --> 01:23:34.804
It's time for the wild and woolly
Top Hand competition.

01:23:34.969 --> 01:23:39.087
Leading off for Glenboro Prison
is New Yorker Skip Donahue...

01:23:39.289 --> 01:23:44.158
... doing time for making a withdrawal
without having an account.

01:23:44.329 --> 01:23:49.119
He told the judge he was just trying
to help New York by using our money.

01:23:49.289 --> 01:23:53.328
-I hope I can remember everything.
-Good luck.

01:23:53.849 --> 01:23:57.046
Thanks. That's very kind of you.

01:24:17.489 --> 01:24:22.279
That's our boy, baby!
That's our boy there!

01:24:28.249 --> 01:24:33.642
What do you say about that, folks?
He's got some cowboy in him, huh?

01:24:33.809 --> 01:24:36.960
He sure does. You old sly bones.

01:24:37.129 --> 01:24:40.201
-Where'd you get him?
-We'll see.

01:24:41.089 --> 01:24:46.163
Next up, five-time winner and current
champion, Caesar Geronimo.

01:24:46.329 --> 01:24:49.844
Got caught selling
some white powder at the border.

01:24:50.009 --> 01:24:53.160
And by white powder,
I don't mean talcum powder.

01:24:53.329 --> 01:24:58.642
His horse is so tough it's already
put 1 1 cowboys in the hospital.

01:24:58.889 --> 01:25:02.120
And that's just by breaking wind
on them.

01:25:38.129 --> 01:25:43.283
All right! That cowboy must have
some real strong glue in the saddle.

01:25:54.409 --> 01:25:58.322
Ladies and gentlemen,
that man of mischief from Oklahoma...

01:25:58.529 --> 01:26:03.762
... Iast year's runner-up is getting set
in chute number five, Ringo Stapelton.

01:26:03.969 --> 01:26:08.281
He's doing 99 years for kidnapping
a trainload of college girls...

01:26:08.489 --> 01:26:12.084
... on their way to a singing
contest in Las Vegas.

01:26:19.209 --> 01:26:25.000
Oh, Ringo's in trouble already. He's
down, and the bull's on top of him!

01:26:34.449 --> 01:26:36.838
Next is Bucky Stillwater...

01:26:37.049 --> 01:26:43.045
... found guilty of misplacing
$4 million worth of insurance money.

01:26:43.249 --> 01:26:45.524
The money was never recovered...

01:26:45.729 --> 01:26:49.642
... which is why Bucky has more friends
among the inmates...

01:26:49.849 --> 01:26:52.966
... than any other prisoner
in the whole system.

01:26:53.169 --> 01:26:57.720
Whatever Bucky wants, old Bucky gets.
Except for parole, that is....

01:27:06.929 --> 01:27:12.481
Don't be too surprised if Bucky's out
in time to enjoy that loot...

01:27:12.689 --> 01:27:15.761
...before old age catches up
with him.

01:28:16.969 --> 01:28:21.918
Third up, out of chute number four,
is the Glenboro Prison entry.

01:28:22.089 --> 01:28:26.765
It's that city slicker again, who's
giving the champ a run for his money.

01:28:26.929 --> 01:28:29.887
Can he keep it up?
We're gonna all find out...

01:28:30.049 --> 01:28:34.167
... whether it's luck or if he's
really got some redneck in him.

01:28:34.329 --> 01:28:38.117
Up on Flapjack, here's Skip Donahue.

01:28:38.289 --> 01:28:41.042
Okay. A little tighter, Jesus.

01:28:41.249 --> 01:28:42.887
-How's that?
-That's it.

01:28:46.329 --> 01:28:47.921
Watch his head.

01:28:51.449 --> 01:28:54.919
-Ready?
-Okay, let's go.

01:28:57.089 --> 01:28:59.284
Open the gate!

01:28:59.569 --> 01:29:02.720
Seem to have ourselves
a problem down here.

01:29:04.169 --> 01:29:06.524
He'll be killed in there!

01:29:08.809 --> 01:29:11.926
Some son of a bitch
put a lock on the gate!

01:30:29.049 --> 01:30:31.438
That New Yorker is full of surprises.

01:30:31.649 --> 01:30:35.164
Now here's last year's champ,
Caesar Geronimo...

01:30:35.329 --> 01:30:39.527
...riding a bull that nobody
can ride for more than 3 seconds.

01:30:39.729 --> 01:30:42.323
A bull by the name of Tornado.

01:31:20.929 --> 01:31:23.807
Now you know why he's
our defending champ.

01:31:24.009 --> 01:31:28.958
Well, folks, take a breather while
the judges tally up the scores.

01:31:29.169 --> 01:31:30.921
We'll pause for the cause...

01:31:31.129 --> 01:31:35.168
...and I'll be back in just a bit
to announce the winner.

01:31:44.289 --> 01:31:47.520
Hold on, folks, we got
ourselves the first...

01:31:47.729 --> 01:31:50.721
...push in the history of the prison
rodeo.

01:31:50.889 --> 01:31:55.087
There ain't gonna be any push.
I was ready for this.

01:32:06.449 --> 01:32:09.168
Ladies and gentlemen,
hold on to your hats.

01:32:09.329 --> 01:32:14.767
As a tiebreaker, both wardens
have okayed the Hard Money event...

01:32:14.929 --> 01:32:18.638
... the single most dangerous
event in all of rodeo competition.

01:32:18.809 --> 01:32:21.323
All you have to do to win this event...

01:32:21.489 --> 01:32:26.517
... is snatch a little sack of money
between the horns of a bull.

01:32:26.689 --> 01:32:32.924
As soon as our two boys get ready,
we'll start our final competition.

01:32:48.809 --> 01:32:52.563
Are you ready for the main event?

01:32:53.169 --> 01:32:57.321
Well, listen to this. Warden Beatty
has just informed me...

01:32:57.489 --> 01:33:01.801
... that he and Warden Sampson
have so much faith in their boys...

01:33:02.009 --> 01:33:05.558
... that instead of splitting the purse
as usual...

01:33:05.769 --> 01:33:08.488
... it'll be a winner-take-all event.

01:33:08.689 --> 01:33:12.523
I'm saying that $50, 000 in bills
is gonna be tied...

01:33:12.689 --> 01:33:16.568
...between the horns of one of the
meanest bulls around.

01:33:16.769 --> 01:33:20.398
And whichever inmate grabs the money
is the winner.

01:33:20.569 --> 01:33:22.844
And here they are,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:33:23.009 --> 01:33:25.443
I get nervous sometimes before
these things.

01:33:25.609 --> 01:33:31.047
-Word is that your warden's a nice guy.
-He's a prick.

01:33:31.209 --> 01:33:37.523
A prick? Boy, did I hear that wrong.
Well, is it true you're an ass-kisser?

01:33:37.689 --> 01:33:42.399
-You're gonna get a punch in the mouth.
-I'm just telling you what I heard.

01:33:42.569 --> 01:33:44.161
I'm an ass-kisser too.

01:33:44.329 --> 01:33:48.720
We're both dumb if no one's gonna
get this money except two pricks.

01:33:48.889 --> 01:33:50.880
Stands to reason, doesn't it?

01:34:21.169 --> 01:34:24.764
I'll distract the bull,
you grab the money. Okay?

01:34:24.929 --> 01:34:27.238
What difference
does it make who wins?

01:34:27.409 --> 01:34:30.003
Why don't we give the cash
to the prisoners?

01:34:30.169 --> 01:34:36.517
I'll tell you what. You do whatever you
think is best, okay? Get ready.

01:36:52.569 --> 01:36:57.597
The winner, and champion for the
sixth time in a row, Caesar Geronimo.

01:36:57.849 --> 01:37:00.522
Goddamn!

01:37:35.089 --> 01:37:38.798
Well, I'll be a monkey's uncle!
That boy's lost his mind.

01:37:38.969 --> 01:37:43.406
Holy cow, there's gonna
be hell to pay for that.

01:37:49.689 --> 01:37:55.605
Now to wrap up our day, here's
the greased-pig sacking contest.

01:39:58.889 --> 01:40:00.083
-Holy shit!
-What?

01:40:04.769 --> 01:40:07.681
What the hell is going--?
Are you okay?

01:40:08.089 --> 01:40:09.522
They're in the camper!

01:40:13.329 --> 01:40:16.958
Look, I'm sorry, but we're
in a real hurry, okay?

01:40:17.169 --> 01:40:19.046
What is going on?

01:40:43.849 --> 01:40:46.568
I'm sorry.
Harry Monroe, Skip Donahue...

01:40:46.729 --> 01:40:49.038
...Rory Schultebrand.

01:40:49.209 --> 01:40:53.725
-My wife, Teresa, and my brother, Ramon.
-Hello.

01:40:53.889 --> 01:40:56.961
-Hey, guys. That is yours.
-Where you guys going?

01:40:57.129 --> 01:40:59.484
Veracruz. We got some family there.

01:40:59.649 --> 01:41:04.006
-Hey, Rory going with you?
-Try to be brave, Sweetpants.

01:41:04.169 --> 01:41:07.764
-Oh, man! Take care.
-Be a good girl, now.

01:41:07.929 --> 01:41:12.127
Ramon! A su casa, honey.
It's me and you!

01:41:18.649 --> 01:41:21.482
He kissed me. Damn!

01:41:31.769 --> 01:41:33.487
Let's go.

01:41:40.809 --> 01:41:43.607
We got to get the hell out of here!

01:42:00.129 --> 01:42:01.960
Wait a minute.

01:42:06.729 --> 01:42:08.685
-How'd you get out?
-We busted out.

01:42:08.849 --> 01:42:10.999
-But you're free!
-You're damn right!

01:42:11.169 --> 01:42:15.959
-No, they caught the other two guys.
-Thanks to Meredith.

01:42:16.129 --> 01:42:17.482
Oh!

01:42:19.489 --> 01:42:24.517
You mean, we're really free?
We're free!

01:42:30.049 --> 01:42:33.405
-You're a hell of a lawyer.
-Thanks. Thanks very much.

01:42:33.569 --> 01:42:36.800
-Good luck.
-Thank you.

01:42:40.969 --> 01:42:44.245
-Thanks for everything.
-It's okay.

01:42:49.929 --> 01:42:51.806
Thank you.

01:42:51.969 --> 01:42:53.607
It's okay.

01:43:03.809 --> 01:43:08.837
Come on. Let's get out of this state
before somebody changes their mind.

01:43:21.449 --> 01:43:25.078
-Aren't you forgetting something?
-What?

01:43:25.329 --> 01:43:28.162
What about my opening night?

01:43:28.329 --> 01:43:30.604
Am I still invited?

01:43:31.609 --> 01:43:35.124
Holy mackerel! How many times
do I have to ask you?

01:43:45.289 --> 01:43:46.608
Come on.

